	<section id="changelog:umc">
		<title>Univention Management Console</title>

		<section id="changelog:umc:web">
			<title>Univention Management Console web interface</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A cross site scripting vulnerability in the &ucsUMC; menu has been fixed (<u:bug>52665</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Package version bump to ensure package update will be done in all scenarios (<u:bug>52371</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The OpenAPI schema has been adjusted to be compliant: The <property>example</property> property of parameters has been removed as it conflicts with <property>examples</property> (<u:bug>52862</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The OpenAPI schema of the UDM REST API now contains <literal>201</literal> as additional possible status code for modify operations.
					It is returned in case an object was moved (<u:bug>52725</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The OpenAPI schema of the UDM REST API now returns <literal>200</literal> as status code for the retrieval of object creation templates (<u:bug>52723</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:portal">
			<title>Univention Portal</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fetching of user information is now done against the Apache HTTP interface instead of directly against the UMC web server (<u:bug>52293</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:server">
			<title>Univention Management Console server</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix translation of a <package>pwdQuality</package> related error message which led to German/English mix in &ucsUMC; (<u:bug>52198</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The &ucsUCRV; <envar>pam/krb5/ticket_after_pwchange</envar> has been added to restore the default behavior of the PAM module <filename>krb5</filename>.
					See <ulink url="https://help.univention.com/t/17403"/> for more information (<u:bug>52188</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A <classname>KeyError</classname> is prevented when a session timer has already been removed (<u:bug>52535</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The evaluation of disallow option pattern in the ACL definitions has been repaired (<u:bug>25197</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A crash of the &ucsUMC; server has been fixed (<u:bug>52699</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A cross site scripting vulnerability has been fixed (<u:bug>52665</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The Python Notifier implementation is used (among others) by the &ucsUMC; server to handle the communication between the main server process and the UMC module processes.
					If any UMC module process fails to start within a few seconds the module process is forcefully terminated by the server process.
					Under high load a fallback implementation is invoked to terminate all child processes, which sometimes is too eager and kills unrelated processes using <command>`python2.7</command>.
					This included UCS services like &ucsUVMM;, UMC server, UMC web server, UMC REST API, UCS Portal server and &ucsS4C;.
					The broken fallback mechanism has been disabled and removed (<u:bug>52518</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The fix addresses a memory leak in <package>univention-management-console-server</package> which was introduced in erratum <u:erratum>848</u:erratum>.
					In addition, a log message was moved from the <property>process</property> to the <property>info</property> log level (<u:bug>52508</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					UMC now shows a banner to the upcoming Univention Summit 2021 once (<u:bug>52499</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The removal of sessions has been optimized (<u:bug>52273</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The UMC web server is now multiprocessing capable (<u:bug>52293</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Data stored for outstanding SAML queries are now removed when a SAML response is received (<u:bug>52444</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					SAML identities are now cached in a BDB database instead of in memory (<u:bug>52442</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Expired sessions are now removed from the SAML cache (<u:bug>52443</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The UMC server is now multiprocessing capable (<u:bug>52371</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:appcenter">
			<title>Univention App Center</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix traceback when using &ucsAppC; once App ini file with install permissions is present in cache (<u:bug>52852</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The app parameter <property>DockerScriptInit</property> can now be configured via &ucsUCR; (<u:bug>52839</u:bug>).
